The House Budget Committee approved apackage of 23 billion dlrs in taxes and budget cuts to reducethe 1988 budget deficit.    The 20-14 party-line vote by the Democratic-controlledcommittee sends the measure to the full House where HouseSpeaker Jim Wright predicted passage next week.    The package--including 12 billion dlrs in taxes PresidentReagan has vowed to veto--was put together by other committeesunder a new budget law requiring a 23 billion dlr cut in thedeficit to scale down the 1988 budget deficit. Reuter&#3;